#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:3
#: 295495b70d9a469e8b2f8e67f4e51b3d
msgid "How to reinstall a template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:6
#: 925bbd4976dc45c0b5f18f9fc03236a4
msgid ""
"If you suspect your :doc:`template </user/templates/templates>` is "
"broken, misconfigured, or compromised, you can reinstall any template "
"that was installed from the Qubes repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:9
#: f6861880095b424497e0de42265094de
msgid "Automatic Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:12
#: 430405f6cb6944fdacf89cad2e766e55
msgid ""
"First, copy any files that you wish to keep from the template’s ``/home``"
" and ``/rw`` folders to a safe storage location. Then, in a dom0 "
"terminal, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:20
#: 6b631f0c25e04677a14a09facb5cf0b9
msgid ""
"Replace ``qubes-template-package-name`` with the name of the *package* of"
" the template you wish to reinstall. For example, use ``qubes-template-"
"fedora-25`` if you wish to reinstall the ``fedora-25`` template. Only one"
" template can be reinstalled at a time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:22
#: 0f51708e71074d8ea618eea3e9928214
msgid ""
"Note that Qubes may initially refuse to perform the reinstall if the "
"exact revision of the template package on your system is no longer in the"
" Qubes online repository. In this case, you can specify ``upgrade`` as "
"the action instead and the newer version will be used. The other ``dnf`` "
"package actions that are supported in addition to ``reinstall`` and "
"``upgrade`` are ``upgrade-to`` and ``downgrade``. Note that the "
"``upgrade``, ``upgrade-to``, and ``downgrade`` commands are only "
"supported under Fedora based UpdateVMs. If you receive a message about "
"them being unsupported, review the manual reinstallation method below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:24
#: 1438b8fac9e54bfda03c3227721b2ea0
msgid ""
"**Reminder:** If you’re trying to reinstall a template that is not in an "
"enabled repo, you must enable that repo. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:32
#: ce6fc6aae19c4a60ab365083c8d234e6
msgid ""
"**Note:** VMs that are using the reinstalled template will not be "
"affected until they are restarted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:35
#: b73d81287d5947549a6a5bc56fffa109
msgid "Manual Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:38
#: a4effde9326e469fa6919fceada427a3
msgid ""
"In what follows, the term “target template” refers to whichever template "
"you want to reinstall. If you want to reinstall more than one template, "
"repeat these instructions for each one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:40
#: d84a37fd9b29488aaac309bd3b5f8058
msgid "Clone the existing target template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:42
#: c27efc032aba49af92bac7df683a03fb
msgid ""
"This can be a good idea if you’ve customized the existing template and "
"want to keep your customizations. On the other hand, if you suspect that "
"this template is broken, misconfigured, or compromised, be certain you do"
" not start any VMs using it in the below procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:46
#: e2660c95c7184970bd13d33f83494943
msgid ""
"Temporarily change all VMs based on the target template to the new clone "
"template, or remove them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:48
#: de37d54023cd45b18396ae9ee8568ee6
msgid ""
"This can be a good idea if you have user data in these VMs that you want "
"to keep. On the other hand, if you suspect that these VMs (or the "
"templates on which they are based) are broken, misconfigured, or "
"compromised, you may want to remove them instead. You can do this in "
"Qubes Manager by right-clicking on the VM and clicking **Remove VM**, or "
"you can use the command ``qvm-remove <vm-name>`` in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:52
#: 95cd05f10d514b79b44e58206847e7b2
msgid "Uninstall the target template from dom0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:59
#: fa195bd301ae40538af418608f9f48eb
msgid "For example, to uninstall the ``whonix-gw`` template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:67
#: 4cae50a2d04942f0954b3ead28bf0433
msgid "Reinstall the target template in dom0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:74
#: 461dbef622464f529be60b681ce3c9fc
msgid "For example, to install the ``whonix-gw`` template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:82
#: 797cca91201c44bfb6fc69be62c8b0f7
msgid ""
"If you temporarily changed all VMs based on the target template to the "
"clone template in step 3, change them back to the new target template "
"now. If you instead removed all VMs based on the old target template, you"
" can recreate your desired VMs from the newly reinstalled target template"
" now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-reinstall-a-template.rst:84
#: baa6233358dd4151babb779d7d9ae458
msgid ""
"Delete the cloned template. You can do this in Qubes Manager by right-"
"clicking on the VM and clicking **Remove VM**, or you can use the command"
" ``qvm-remove <vm-name>`` in dom0."
msgstr ""

